                            "year": 2021
                        }
                    },
                    "company": "Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam (VU Amsterdam)",
                    "description": "My dissertation is on religion and international relations theory. It consists of three parts. In the first part I set out the position of the so-called religionists who argue that a new paradigm is needed. In the second part, I introduce the political realists Morgenthau and Waltz and I investigate to what extent they have neglected religion. My conclusion is that the religionists have overlooked the 'Augustinian' moments in political realism and therefore unjustifiably argue that religion has been omitted by IR theory and that it should be incorporated. In the third part, I present an alternative to integrate religion into theorizing on IR.",
